 VERDICT: the contrastive W_c learns RELEVANCE RANKING that generalizes (the right
 episode tops the list for unseen phrasings — neither the centroid nor raw q.K could
 do this), but the absolute-magnitude FOREIGN-REJECT threshold OVERFITS from 5 training
 negatives (a held-out foreign outscores the weakest held-out positive). In-sample
 gate#1 GREEN was real for the MECHANISM + the O_K-integer exactness, but the open-world
 reject does not generalize at N=3 episodes / 5 foreign.
 => DO NOT deploy the hot path on this W_c. Next levers: (1) far more negative/foreign
 diversity to learn a general reject boundary; (2) decouple reject from the learned
 magnitude — use the ranking for SHORTLIST + a retrieve-and-verify reject (Ring-3 gist
 shortlist -> Ring-2/C2 #222 exact verify), the two-stage design already in the contract.
 Honest-negative #3, but the most informative: RANKING is learnable+generalizes; the
 THRESHOLD/reject is the unsolved part.
